# Data types Smart Pointers: dictates that the data will be store in the heap instead of the stack
# Box<T>: 
# 	  - when we have a trail that can't be computed at compile time
# 	  - on recursive data time, if we have a struct that contains a field of the same struct type
# Rc<T>: Reference Counter, if a variable needs to be use in more than 1 place at the same time
# Arc<T>: Atomic Reference Counter, if needed to use Send Trait to send it to a thread (is thread safe)
# RefCell<T>
# 

